definition.value: An organic chloride salt having nitro blue tetrazolium(2+) as the counterion.
A quinazoline alkaloid that is a marine toxin isolated from fish such as puffer fish. It has been shown to exhibit potential neutotoxicity due to its ability to block voltage-gated sodium channels.

A pyrazolopyrimidine that is pyrazolo[1,5-a]pyrimidine substituted by ethyl, (2S)-2-(2-hydroxyethyl)piperidin-1-yl, and [(1-oxidopyridin-3-yl)methyl]amino groups at positions 3, 5, and 7, respectively. It is a potent pan-cyclin dependent kinase inhibitor that exhibits antineoplastic activity.
